\b0 \cf0 {\listtext	1.	}Customize your theme with a few items that are required to get your theme up and running.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	2.	}Go to \'91Appearance > Customize\'92 and confirm that your site name and tagline are correct (you may need to add a tagline to replace the generic one provided by WordPress).\
{\listtext	3.	}You will have the option to customize other features such as header background images, layout settings, social links, etc. at \'93Appearance > Current Theme Options\'94.\
{\listtext	4.	}In order for the navigation to work you\'92ll need to go set it up within the WordPress administration. There are two menus used in the UMC theme, the top and bottom menus. Both are required to be setup in order for the theme to function properly.\
{\listtext	5.	}Go to \'91Appearance > Menus\'92 and click on the option to \'93create a new menu\'94. It may make sense to name this first menu \'91Top Menu\'92 or \'91Main Navigation\'92. After you\'92ve clicked the Create Menu button you\'92ll see an option to select a theme location. Click the checkbox titled, \'91Primary Menu\'92, and then click the \'93Save Menu\'94 button.\
{\listtext	6.	}Repeat this step for the bottom or footer menu, naming it something logical like \'91Bottom Menu\'92 or \'91Footer Menu\'92. Be sure to click the checkbox for \'91Footer Menu\'92 this time.\
{\listtext	7.	}At this point it\'92s assumed you have a working knowledge of how to build out your menu within WordPress. As you start adding pages and posts you can add those pages into your menu hierarchy.\
{\listtext	8.	}Activate your plugins and start creating content.\
{\listtext	9.	}The plugins package provided by UMC are only suggested plugins and not necessary for the theme to function, however they greatly enhance the capabilities of the theme and the variety of display options. The supported Utah plugins are all titled, \'93Utah - \{ plugin name \}\'94.\
{\listtext	10.	}To really utilize the Tribal Database plugins' capabilities it is necessary to install and activate the \'93Custom sidebars\'94 plugin. Custom sidebars allows you to create as many widget area as you want and to include a widget on a single page/post, or categories, etc. The UMC Theme supports 5 widget areas that are automatically included on each page. You\'92ll need to setup and configure these sidebar areas.\
{\listtext	11.	}Activate the Custom sidebars plugin by first, making sure you have placed it in your \'91/wp-content/plugins\'92 directory, and then going to \'91Plugins\'92 in the WordPress admin. Go ahead and activate the plugin.\
{\listtext	12.	}You\'92ll need to configure the custom sidebars widget by going to \'93Appearance > Custom Sidebars\'94.\
{\listtext	13.	}You\'92ll need to select which sidebars are available for substitution. You\'92ll see a list in the top-left of the page that allows you to select different sidebar areas. Select the following four options:\
