2.  Installing and activating the Revolution Slider for the home page\
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls5\ilvl0
\b0 \cf0 {\listtext	1.	}In the wp-admin go to the Plugins section. In here, make sure that you have the \'93Revolution Slider\'94 plugin activated. If you don\'92t see the plugin, look inside the setup folder we have provided and copy and paste this into your /wp-content/plugins directory\
{\listtext	2.	}Once activated, go to the new \'93Revolution Slider\'94 section in the wp-admin.\
{\listtext	3.	}Import the home page header slider template by clicking on the \'93Import Slider\'94 button (green and to the right after the list of sliders). Search for the home page header slider template by looking inside the setup folder inside the tribaldb folder. Select the home_header_slider.zip file and click \'93Import Slider\'94. (You do want to overwrite any custom styles).\
{\listtext	4.	}Once the home page header slider is uploaded, click on the title to go to the slider settings page. It is best to not change any of these options unless you know what you are doing.\
{\listtext	5.	}From here, edit the individual slides by clicking on the \'93Edit Slides\'94 button (blue button at the bottom of the main slider setting section).\
{\listtext	6.	}You will see a list of slides. These are sample/template slides. Click \'93Edit Slide\'94. \
{\listtext	7.	}There are only a couple things you need to change in order to get your slide setup. Once you have it how you would like, click \'93Update Slide\'94 at the bottom or the green cycle icon on the right side. To preview, click the magnify glass icon.\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\pardirnatural
\ls5\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}
\b To change the background image
\b0 , select the \'93Change Image\'94 button in the Slider Main Image / Background section. To accommodate large computer screens, the best size of image to upload is 1920 px wide by 1080 px high. Save this image at the lowest compression possible to keep file size down.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}
\b To change the title text
\b0 , under the Layers Timing  & Sorting select layer 1. Change the text inside the Layer Content Section. Same idea for the subtitle. Once again, do not change anything else unless you know what you are doing.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}
\b To change the position of the header title or subtile
\b0  simply drag to the position you would like.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}
\b To change the style of the text
\b0 , select one of the four option in the style drop down. \'93left-bar\'94 means that the text will have the background bar extend all the way to the left of the screen. Same idea for the right, only to the right. \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}
\b If you wanted a left and right bar
\b0 , you need to select \'93Add Layer\'94 at the bottom of the slide, select the appropriate style for that layer and position appropriately.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	8.	}To add this slideshow to the home page, go to Appearance>Current Theme Options. Under General Options, select \'91Home Page\'92 to include the revolution slider on the home page. NOTE: The Slider Alias must be \'93home_header_slider\'94 for this to work.\
{\listtext	9.	}That\'92s it! You\'92ve got the Revolution Slider setup for the home page.\
