\b \cf0 4.  Adding a parallax background section to a page\
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls7\ilvl0
\b0 \cf0 {\listtext	1.	}This only works on a page that is using the \'93default\'94 page template, which is a full-width page template.\
{\listtext	2.	}Go to the plugins section and make sure the \'93Parallax Scroll by Adamrob.co.uk\'94 is activated. If not, you can find the plugin in the mu-plugins folder in the tribaldb folder. Copy and paste this plugin into the wp-content/plugins folder and activate it.\
{\listtext	3.	}Go to the new \'93Parallax Scroll\'94 section. Click on \'93Add New\'94\
{\listtext	4.	}To add the Parallax Scroll background image, you will add it via the featured image. (i.e. the featured image will be your background image)\
{\listtext	5.	}Inside the editor you can add whatever content you would like.\
{\listtext	6.	}For options, you can set a specific height (in px). Make sure to select the Full Width option. The rest don\'92t change unless you know what you\'92re doing.\
{\listtext	7.	}Select \'93Publish\'94 when you are done.\
{\listtext	8.	}Go back to the main \'93Parallax Scroll\'94 section by clicking on it again.\
{\listtext	9.	}Copy the shortcake you are given and add this inside the editor of the page you would like to add it to.\
{\listtext	10.	}Publish that page and voila! That parallax scroll section has been added  to your page.\
